'''Chester Clute''' (February 18, 1891 – April 2, 1956) was an [[United States|American]] [[actor]] familiar in scores of [[Hollywood]] films from his debut in 1930. Diminutive, bald-pated with a bristling moustache, he appeared in mostly unbilled roles, consisting usually of one or two lines, in nearly 250 films. He died of a heart attack aged 65. Born Chester Lamont Clute in Orange, New Jersey. He died in Woodland Hills, California and is buried at [[Valhalla Memorial Park Cemetery]].
